# Vercel Web Analytics Implementation

## Summary
Successfully installed and configured Vercel Web Analytics for the Next.js project following the latest official documentation from https://vercel.com/docs/analytics/quickstart.

## Changes Made

### 1. Package Installation
- **File Modified**: `package.json`
- **Action**: Added `@vercel/analytics` package as a dependency
- **Command Used**: `npm install @vercel/analytics`

### 2. Analytics Integration
- **File Modified**: `frontend/app/layout.js`
- **Changes**:
  - Added import: `import { Analytics } from '@vercel/analytics/next';`
  - Added `<Analytics />` component at the end of the `<body>` tag
- **Pattern Used**: Next.js App Router pattern (as detected from project structure)

### 3. Lock File Update
- **File Modified**: `package-lock.json`
- **Action**: Automatically updated by npm to reflect the new @vercel/analytics dependency and its 346 sub-dependencies

## Implementation Details

The project uses Next.js 16.2.10 with the App Router pattern. Following the official Vercel documentation, the Analytics component was added to the root layout file (`app/layout.js`) as recommended for App Router projects.

The implementation follows this pattern from the docs:
```javascript
import { Analytics } from '@vercel/analytics/next';
// ... added to body alongside children
```

This ensures that analytics tracking will be active across all pages of the application.

## Verification Steps Completed

1. ✅ **Build Verification**: Ran `npm run build` - Build completed successfully with no errors
2. ✅ **Linter Check**: Ran `npm run lint` - No new errors introduced (1 pre-existing warning in unrelated file)
3. ✅ **Dependencies**: Updated package-lock.json reflects all 346 packages from @vercel/analytics
4. ✅ **Git Staging**: All modified files (app/layout.js, package.json, package-lock.json) staged for commit

## Next Steps

After deployment to Vercel:
1. Enable Web Analytics in the Vercel dashboard (Analytics section → Enable button)
2. Deploy the changes using `vercel deploy`
3. Verify tracking is active by checking browser Network tab for requests to `/<unique-path>/view`

## Notes

- No breaking changes introduced
- Existing code structure and functionality preserved
- Analytics component placed at the end of body tag as recommended by Vercel docs
- The analytics will automatically track page views and web vitals once deployed to Vercel
